@startuml cgs-training-2-processing-pipeline
' ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
' ║  CGS TRAINING DIAGRAM 2/4 — THE PROCESSING PIPELINE                   ║
' ║  "What happens when a message enters CGS?"                             ║
' ║  Step-by-step with database tables and real examples                   ║
' ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

title **CGS Processing Pipeline — Step by Step**\n//What happens inside CGS when a message arrives?//\n<size:11>Example: CBB sends a StUF-BG notification that a citizen moved → fans out to 19 providers</size>

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam activityBorderColor #37474F
skinparam activityBackgroundColor #ECEFF1

|#E8F5E9| Consumer Application |
start
:A consumer app (e.g. **CBB**)
sends a SOAP message to CGS;
note right
  The message arrives on one of
  CGS's published endpoints:
  
  ""https://[server]:8443/CGS/""
  ""  StUF/services/BGAsynchroon""
  
  Port **8443** for normal services
  Port **8444** for Digikoppeling/ebMS
end note

|#E3F2FD| CGS Service Bus |

:== STEP 1: Configuration Validation ==
Check: Does this service exist? 
Is the message syntactically valid?;
note right
  **Reads:** `servicedefinition` (220 services)
  **Reads:** `servicecomponentrelation` (5852 wirings)
  
  Finds: service = "StUFOntvangAsynchroonBG"
  Handling = **ASYN** (asynchronous)
  QoS = **EXACTLYONCE** (guaranteed delivery)
end note

if (Service exists and is ACTIVE?) then (yes)
else (no)
  :Return SOAP Fault;
  |#E8F5E9| Consumer Application |
  stop
endif

|#E3F2FD| CGS Service Bus |

:== STEP 2: Authorization ==
Is CBB allowed to call this service?;
note right
  **Reads:** `serviceusage` (660 authorizations)
  
  Lookup: application=CBB
           + service=StUFOntvangAsynchroonBG
  
  Also checks **usage level**:
  • **Production** → uses production endpoint config
  • **Test** → uses test endpoint config
end note

if (Authorized?) then (yes)
else (no)
  :Return "Not Authorized" fault;
  |#E8F5E9| Consumer Application |
  stop
endif

|#E3F2FD| CGS Service Bus |

:== STEP 3: Message Matching ==
What kind of message is this?;
note right
  **Reads:** `messagedefinition` (2065 types)
  
  Matching strategy (in order):
  1. **SOAPAction** header
  2. **Namespace** + **messagekey**
  3. **XPath filter** expression
  4. **Element value**
  
  Example match:
  namespace = ""http://www.egem.nl/StUF/sector/bg/0204""
  messagekey = ""kennisgevingsBericht""
  → This is a **StUF-BG notification** about a
     person change (birth, move, death, etc.)
end note

:== STEP 4: Message Validation ==
Is the message content valid?;
note right
  **Reads:** `validator`, `validatoraction`
  
  Only if service has **validation enabled**.
  Checks XML structure against
  message definition rules.
  
  If invalid → log error + return fault
end note

if (Valid message?) then (yes)
else (no)
  :Return validation error
  with detailed error description;
  |#E8F5E9| Consumer Application |
  stop
endif

|#E3F2FD| CGS Service Bus |

:== STEP 5: Dynamic Routing ==
Where should this message go?
(This is where the magic happens!);
note right
  **Reads:** `channeldefinition` (532 channels)
  
  For **StUFOntvangAsynchroonBG**:
  **29 routing channels** evaluated!
  
  Each channel has filters:
  • **Provider filter**: "send to CMG only"
  • **Message filter**: "only kennisgevings"
  • **XPath filter**: content-based routing
  • **Organisation filter**: source/target org
  
  **Fan-out rule**: message goes to
  ALL channels whose filters match.
  
  Result: up to **19 providers** receive
  their own copy of this notification!
end note

:Selected channels:
→ CMG (Broker Data)
→ GEOTAX (Tax Geography)
→ CWIZ
→ CGA (Addresses)
→ iBurgerzaken
→ iSamenleving
→ CML, WebNext, Corsa...
→ **19 total providers**;

|#FFF3E0| Per Channel (repeated for each matched route) |

:== STEP 6: Transformation ==
Does the provider speak a different format?;
note right
  **Reads:** `transformationdefinition` (993 rules)
  
  Common transformations:
  • **StUF BG 0204 → StUF BG 0210**
    (legacy Centric format)
  • **StUF BG 0204 → StUF BG 0310**
    (current standard)
  • **Bv04 → Bv03** (broker confirmation
    → application confirmation)
  
  Each transformation uses an **XSLT**
  stylesheet stored in `xsltcontent`
end note

if (Is ASYNC service?) then (yes — ASYNC)
  :== Queue Storage ==
  Place message in **sending queue**
  (Exactly Once = guaranteed delivery);
  note right
    **Runtime only** — no config table.
    
    Checks `applicationopeningperiod`:
    Is the target app currently "open"?
    • **Open** → deliver immediately
    • **Closed** → hold in queue until
      opening period starts
    
    Note: SYNC messages ignore
    opening periods and always
    deliver immediately!
  end note
  
  :Wait for application to be open;
  
else (no — SYNC)
endif

|#FCE4EC| Delivery to Provider |

:== STEP 7: Delivery ==
Send message via the right protocol;
note right
  **Reads:** `adapterdefinition` → protocol type
  **Reads:** `adapterendpoint` → connection point
  **Reads:** `endpointconfiguration` → URL, credentials
  **Reads:** `certificate` → TLS/signing cert
  
  **10 protocol types available:**
  ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
  WEBSERVICE (99 adapters) → SOAP/HTTP
  JAVA (23) → Internal JVM call
  HTTP (10) → REST-like calls
  ABAP (4) → SAP JCo connector
  UNIFACE (4) → via STUNNEL proxy
  MQ (3) → IBM MQ queue
  FTP (2) → File transfer
  ebMS (2) → Digikoppeling
  REST (1) → REST API
  FILE (1) → Local file system
end note

:Provider receives message
(e.g. CMG processes the BG notification);

|#F3E5F5| Logging & Audit |

:== Throughout: Complete Audit Trail ==
Every step is logged;
note right
  **Writes to 4 log tables:**
  
  `logservicerequest` — WHO called WHAT
    consumer=CBB, service=StUFOntvangAsynchroonBG
    
  `logroute` — WHERE it was sent
    provider=CMG, endpoint=CMG_STUF
    
  `logaction` — WHAT happened at each step
    ConfigValidation✓, Authorization✓,
    MessageMatch✓, Routing✓, Delivery✓
    
  `logmessage` — WHAT was the content
    Original XML, transformed XML,
    response XML (if logging enabled)
  
  **Visible in CGS Dashboard** — auto-refreshing
  monitoring with traffic counts, error rates,
  and drill-down to individual messages
end note

stop

@enduml

