note bottom of transform_engine
  **Why transformations exist:**
  
  Different applications were built at different times
  and support different StUF versions:
  
  • **Old SAP apps** (CBB, CGA, CIN...) → StUF BG **0204**
  • **New apps** (modern portals) → StUF BG **0310**
  • **Centric apps** → StUF BG **0210**
  
  When CBB sends a notification in StUF 0204 format,
  CGS automatically transforms it to 0210 for apps
  that need 0210, and to 0310 for apps that need 0310.
  
  **Without CGS:** each app would need N×N adapters
  **With CGS:** each app speaks its own language,
  CGS translates in the middle.
  
  This is the core value proposition of the ESB.
end note

note right of fault_msgs
  **Fo03Bericht is #1 most used message**
  
  Every failed service call returns a
  StUF 0301 Fo03 fault message.
  It's used 2431 times across all
  service component relations — more
  than any request or response type.
  
  This means **fault handling is the
  single most configured aspect
  of CGS**. Every service needs
  to know how to report errors.
end note

